'''Tijjani Martinus Jan Reijnders ''' ({{IPA|nl|tiˈdʒaːni ˈrɛi̯ndərs||label=Dutch pronunciation:}}; born 29 July 1998) is a Dutch professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].

After representing various Dutch junior teams, Reijnders began his career with his hometown club, [[PEC Zwolle]], before moving to fellow Dutch club [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]] in the 2017–18 season. He was then loaned to [[RKC Waalwijk]] until the conclusion of the 2019–20 campaign, returning to AZ as a mainstay. He signed for [[AC Milan]] in the summer of 2023 and won the [[2024–25 Supercoppa Italiana]]. After two years at the Italian club, he signed for Manchester City in 2025.

Reijnders is a Dutch international, having progressed from the [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|under-20]] level onwards. He made his senior international debut for the country in September 2023.

==Club career==
===Early career===
Reijnders started his career with the [[FC Twente|Twente]] youth team. He played at Twente until the U-17 team before being released to CSV '28 and playing for one year from 2015 to 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Profil Tijjani Reijnders, Gelandang Andalan Eredivisie Keturunan Indonesia|url=https://jakarta.swarakyat.id/2022/02/profil-tijjani-reijnders-gelandang.html|access-date=11 February 2022|language=id}}</ref>

In 2016, Reijnders joined his hometown team [[PEC Zwolle]] U-19 where he then moved up the level and appeared in the Eredivisie club's first team.

===AZ===
In 2017, development of his career accelerated rapidly. From working at a local Aldi supermarket and training in Zwolle, he crossed over to AZ's Under-21 team and moved up to the first professional team in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Reijnders promoveert naar A-selectie |url=https://www.az.nl/nl/nieuws/reijnders-promoveert-naar-a-selectie |access-date=15 July 2023 |website=www.az.nl |language=en}}</ref>

In 2020, he was loaned to [[RKC Waalwijk]] for six months, from January to June.<ref>{{Cite web |title=RKC Waalwijk huurt middenvelder Tijjani Reijnders van AZ |url=https://www.bd.nl/rkc-waalwijk/rkc-waalwijk-huurt-middenvelder-tijjani-reijnders-van-az~a3367ac94/ |access-date=15 July 2023 |website=BD}}</ref> Afterwards, Reijnders returned to AZ and became part of the first team, in which he managed to play in the [[2022–23 UEFA Europa Conference League|2022–23 Europa Conference League]] semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/alkmaar-gegen-west-ham-2023-europa-conference-league-4839351/spielbericht|title=Glanzlos, aber effizient: West Ham schlägt Alkmaar und steht im Endspiel|publisher=Kicker|language=de|date=18 May 2023}}</ref> Reijnders was named to the [[Eredivisie]] Team of the Month in September 2022 and April 2023.

===AC Milan===
On 19 July 2023, Reijnders joined [[Serie A]] club [[AC Milan]], signing a five-year contract until June 2028.<ref>{{cite web |date=19 July 2023 |title=Official Statement: Tijjani Reijnders |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2023-07-19/official-statement-tijjani-reijnders |access-date=19 July 2023 |publisher=[[AC Milan]]}}</ref> On 21 August, he made his first competitive start for Rossoneri in a Serie A match against [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=21 August 2023 |title=Bologna 0–2 AC Milan (Aug 21, 2023) |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/679225 |access-date=11 November 2023 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On 11 November, in a Serie A match against [[US Lecce|Lecce]] at the [[Stadio Via del mare]], Reijnders scored his debut goal for Milan.<ref>{{Cite web |date=11 November 2023 |title=Lecce 2–2 AC Milan (Nov 11, 2023) |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/679337 |access-date=11 November 2023 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On 3 March 2025, AC Milan announced that Tijjani Reijnders had signed a contract extension, committing to the club until 30 June 2030.<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 March 2025 |title=OFFICIAL STATEMENT: TIJJANI REIJNDERS |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2025-03-03/official-statement-tijjani-reijnders |access-date=3 March 2025 |publisher=AC Milan |language=en}}</ref>

Reijnders was listed on the [[2024–25 Serie A#Awards|2024–25 Serie A Team of the Season]] and was named the [[Serie A Awards|Serie A Best Midfielder]] of the season.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":17">{{Cite web |last=Arts |first=Electronic |date=2025-05-16 |title=Serie A Enilive Team of the Season (TOTS) – EA SPORTS FC™ Ultimate Team – EA SPORTS Official Site |url=https://www.ea.com/games/ea-sports-fc/fc-25/tots/serie-a |access-date=2025-05-16 |website=Electronic Arts Inc. |language=en}}</ref>

===Manchester City===
On 11 June 2025, [[Premier League]] club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] announced the signing of Reijnders on a five-year deal reportedly worth £46.5m.<ref>{{cite web |date=11 June 2025 |title=City sign Netherlands midfielder Reijnders |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-sign-tijjani-reijnders-ac-milan-transfer-63885221 |access-date=11 June 2025 |publisher=[[Manchester City F.C.]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Coates |first=Charlotte |date=11 June 2025 |title=Man City confirm £46.5m signing of Reijnders |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c0mr3dp2g8yo |access-date=11 June 2025 |publisher=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref> On 16 August, Reijnders made his league debut for the club in a 4–0 away win against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]], scoring the second goal of the game and assisting [[Erling Haaland]] for the third.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hafez |first=Shamoon |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c2077030850t |title=Wolves 0–4 Man City: Reijnders and Haaland shine as Man City thrash Wolves |website=BBC Sport |date=16 August 2025 |access-date=16 August 2025}}</ref> On 22 March 2026, Reijnders won his first trophy for the club, the [[EFL Cup final|Carabao Cup]], beating [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] 2-0 in the final.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Athletic |first=The |date=2026-03-22 |title=Arsenal vs Manchester City live updates: Nico O'Reilly strikes twice in Carabao Cup final |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/arsenal-vs-manchester-city-live-updates-carabao-cup-final-score-result/xHOGP3Tod4II/ |access-date=2026-03-22 |website=The Athletic |language=en-US}}</ref>

==International career==
Prior to receiving his first call-up to the Dutch senior team in June 2023 for the [[2023 UEFA Nations League Finals|UEFA Nations League Finals]], Reijnders was also eligible to represent Indonesia through his mother's lineage, but he chose to represent his birth country.<ref>{{cite news |date=29 May 2023 |title=Oranjeselectie voor de UEFA Nations League Finals |trans-title=National team squad for the Nations League Finals |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/nederlands-elftal/80805/oranjeselectie-voor-de-uefa-nations-league-finals |access-date=29 May 2023 |language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Arifin |first=Asad |date=1 November 2024 |title=Tijjani Reijnders yang sangat bangga punya darah Indonesia. |trans-title=Tijjani Reijnders is very proud to have Indonesian blood |url=https://www.bola.net/tim_nasional/tijjani-reijnders-yang-sangat-bangga-punya-darah-indonesia-ad98d9.html |access-date=27 May 2025 |website=bola.net |language=id}}</ref>

On 7 September 2023, Reijnders made his Netherlands debut as a substitute in a 3–0 win over [[Greece national football team|Greece]] in a [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|UEFA Euro 2024 qualifier]].<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/internationals/2023-09-08/reijnders-debuts-with-the-netherlands-victory-for-kjaer|title= REIJNDERS DEBUTS WITH THE NETHERLANDS, VICTORY FOR KJÆR|date=7 September 2023|access-date=19 November 2023|website=A.C. Milan}}</ref> On 13 October, he made his first start as the Netherlands were defeated 2–1 by [[France national football team|France]] in the same competition.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20231015_96184265|title=Met mes op de keel, maar toch trekt Oranje vol vertrouwen naar Griekenland: "We hadden een goede mentaliteit tegen Frankrijk"|date=16 October 2023|access-date=19 November 2023|language=Dutch|website=Het Nieuwsblad}}</ref>

Reijnders scored his first senior international goal in a 4–0 win over [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] at the [[Johan Cruyff Arena]] on 22 March 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68544498|title=Netherlands 4–0 Scotland: Steve Clarke's side given Euro 2024 warning in heavy defeat|date=22 March 2024|access-date=12 June 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

On 29 May 2024, Reijnders was named in the Netherlands' squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5526712/2024/05/29/netherlands-euro-2024-squad-confirmed/|title= Netherlands Euro 2024 squad: Ian Maatsen dropped, Georginio Wijnaldum and Daley Blind retained |date=29 May 2024|access-date=7 June 2024|website=The New York Times}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Reijnders is a mobile central midfielder with a penchant for going forward into the final third and the opposition's penalty area, to either make attempts at scoring or to press opponents.

Upon his transfer to Milan, he was immediately integrated into the team's starting XI by manager [[Stefano Pioli]] as a left-sided central midfielder, known as ''mezzala'' in Italy, in a 4–3–3 formation. He also played as part of the double pivot in a 4–2–3–1 formation, again primarily on the left despite being right-footed.

According to Reijnders, tactical reasons played a somewhat significant role in him choosing AC Milan over [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] as his proposed playing position in the latter team would have limited his movement.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://sempremilan.com/reijnders-role-pioli-milan-over-barcelona | title=Reijnders talks role under Pioli, team-mates and choosing Milan over Barcelona | date=22 December 2023 }}</ref>

==Personal life==
Reijnders is the son of the former footballer [[Martin Reijnders]], as well as the older brother of [[Eliano Reijnders]], a professional footballer who currently plays for [[Persib Bandung]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.peperbus.nl/nieuws/algemeen/1020104/reijnders-in-voetspoor-vader|title=Reijnders in voetspoor vader|website=www.peperbus.nl}}</ref> Reijnders is of Indonesian descent through his [[Moluccans|Moluccan]] mother.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moesson.com/magazines-lijst/interviews/broederliefde/|title=Broederliefde – Interview with Tijjani and Eliano Reijnders|date=June 2021}}</ref> He was named after former [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] and [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] forward [[Tijani Babangida]].<ref>https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/tijjani-reijnders-10-things-man-city-63885225</ref>

